[SN]TITLE[SN]
Feeding Hong Kong's poor and hungry

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
In the restaurant business, owners generally raise their prices when their costs rise - namely rent, and ingredients.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
10 February 2016 Last updated at 01:21 GMT
And Hong Kong ranks among one of the most expensive cities in the world.
But Chan Cheuk Ming has kept the pricing at his eatery unchanged for around 7 years, and works with a charity to feed the poor and hungry.
